Hiring Solutions revenue represented 50% of total revenue in Q4 2011, compared to 44% in the fourth quarter of 2010. http:// dcl.sr/jD

Mobile visits account for more than 15% of total unique member visits and is the fastest growing service on LinkedIn. http:// dcl.sr/j9
As of now, there are more than 50K developers using LinkedIn APIs to help build and power the professional Web. http:// dcl.sr/j7
We also introduced a wave of new products all designed around Identity, Insights, and Everywhere. http:// dcl.sr/j5
We also opened 7 offices outside the U.S. in 2011, bringing the total number of global offices to 22. http:// dcl.sr/j3
We launched 8 local languages last year and in 2012 we’ve added Czech and Dutch to the list, bringing our total to 16. http:// dcl.sr/j1
More than 60 million new professionals have joined LinkedIn since the start of 2011. http:// dcl.sr/iz
And member page views in Q4 grew faster still, at 77%, marking a healthy progression in our key engagement metrics. http:// dcl.sr/ix
Unique member visits to LinkedIn in Q4 grew 67% year over year, even faster than the rate of membership growth. http:// dcl.sr/iv
Our cumulative membership grew 60% year over year to 145 million at the end of the fourth quarter. http:// dcl.sr/ir
For 2011, revenues were a record $522M, up 115%, and we delivered adjusted EBITDA of $99M, or a non-GAAP EPS of 35c. http:// dcl.sr/ip
For Q4, overall revenues grew 105% to a record $168M. http:// dcl.sr/in
